25|$|The op-amp is {{one type}} of <b>differential</b> <b>amplifier.</b> Other types of <b>differential</b> <b>amplifier</b> include the fully <b>differential</b> <b>amplifier</b> (similar to the op-amp, but with two outputs), the {{instrumentation}} amplifier (usually built from three op-amps), the isolation amplifier (similar to the instrumentation amplifier, but with tolerance to common-mode voltages that would destroy an ordinary op-amp), and negative-feedback amplifier (usually built from one or more op-amps and a resistive feedback network).|$|E
