50|$|Modern <b>differential</b> <b>amplifiers</b> {{are usually}} {{implemented}} {{with a basic}} two-transistor circuit called a “long-tailed” pair or differential pair. This circuit was originally implemented using a pair of vacuum tubes. The circuit works the same way for all three-terminal devices with current gain. The “long tail” resistor circuit bias points are largely determined by Ohm's Law and less so by active component characteristics.|$|R
